{
  "_doc": "Avatar: The Last Airbender (code TLA) — Universes Beyond set. Source: https://magic.wizards.com/en/news/feature/collecting-avatar-the-last-airbender . Lineup is Play Boosters + Collector Boosters only (no Draft). Percentages taken verbatim from the article's odds tables. Approximations: Wizards distinguishes many 'Booster Fun' frames (scene, field notes, battle pose, elemental frame, Saga, raised-foil) and separate printings (source material, Jumpstart/Beginner-Box 'TLE' reprints) that have no dedicated Scryfall sub-set code we model here, so those are approximated against the main TLA pool with the nearest available filter: scene/battle-pose/elemental-frame/source-material -> 'showcase', field notes -> 'showcase' (no field_notes art exists for this set), extended-art -> 'extended_art'. Two specifically-named premium finishes are targeted exactly via promo_types instead of the borderless/showcase stand-in: the borderless raised-foil Avatar Aang chase -> 'raised_foil', and the textless neon-ink-foil borderless battle-pose card -> 'neon_ink'. Full-art lands use basicLand + basic_land. Sub-percentages the article reports as 'less than 1%' are entered as 0.5. AUDIT 2026-06: special-finish outcome rarities corrected to match the actual printed sheets (pool-verified): neon_ink->rare. AUDIT 2026-06: Source Material outcomes re-mapped showcase->booster_fun (TLA source material = the 10 boosterfun-promo commons) and Scene outcomes showcase->borderless (TLA scenes carry inverted+borderless, no showcase effect). AUDIT 2026-06 part 2: Source Material outcomes re-mapped to the borderless filter (the article names them ‘Borderless Source Material Cards’; 61-card sheet) and the commons-slot rate converted from per-pack (1 in 26 boosters) to per-slot (0.64% across 6 commons). The earlier booster_fun remap was wrong — TLA’s boosterfun-promo commons are its full-art basic lands.",
